Lead Conversion Components

Use the Leads Conversion components to get a comprehensive view of your lead pipeline. They include a Lead Pipeline chart, Leads by Time chart, Lead Conversion Rate by Lead Source chart, Open Lead Distribution by Lead Source chart, and Summary Metrics.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Developer Edition and for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.
Leads Conversion Overview

The Lead Conversion components contain these charts:

Summary Metrics: Use this chart in places where you want to see a quick summary of your leads.
Lead Pipeline Chart: Visualize opportunities by pipeline stage in terms of the number of leads or revenue. Use the pipeline chart to track changes over time.
Key Performance Indicators:
- Count of new leads from the Lead object.
- Conversion Rate: Total converted leads / total leads.
- Percentage of Open Leads: Indicates the percentage of leads that are in the Open stage.
- Percentage of Total Leads by Lead Source: Indicates the percentage of leads created from a specific source.
- Lead Conversion Rate by Source: Indicates the conversion rate of leads generated from each source.

The chart uses this Salesforce object: Lead.
title: Lead Conversion Components in CRM Analytics
